{
  "files": [
    {"repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express", "path": "lib/request.js"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express", "path": "test/req.host.js"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express", "path": "History.md"}
  ],
  "text": "The Express.js repository contains three source files that reference the deprecated req.host property. First, lib/request.js (lines 452-456) contains the actual definition of the deprecated property, where it is implemented as a getter function using deprecate.function() with the deprecation message 'req.host: Use req.hostname instead'. The file also includes a TODO comment indicating that req.host should be changed to return host in the next major version. Second, test/req.host.js contains comprehensive test cases for the deprecated req.host property, with multiple test suites (lines 7-156) that verify its behavior in various scenarios including handling the Host header, stripping port numbers, working with IPv6 literals, and respecting the 'trust proxy' setting. Third, History.md documents the history of req.host across multiple releases, including: the addition of req.hostname as the correct replacement (line 1284), the deprecation of req.host in favor of req.hostname (line 1286), fixes for req.host when using trust proxy hops count (line 799), fixes for IPv6 literals (line 1436), X-Forwarded-Host support (line 2552), and the initial addition of req.host (line 2726). These files were identified by precise matching of the req.host property usage pattern, excluding false positives from the req.hostname property which is the current, non-deprecated API."
}

